Chemical Process Supervisor/Engineer

Richardson Electronics Ltd

- Lafox, IL 60147

Richardson Electronics (REL) is a global provider of engineered solutions and electronic components to the electron device markets. This position is based in our corporate offices in Lafox, Illinois.
Functional Scope: Under general supervision, establishes and implements chemical processes. Provides expertise and consulting in chemical processing and waste treatment of operations. Supervises hourly personnel and recommends practices in the handling and disposal of hazardous materials and waste. Responsible for training of direct reports and others involved in chemical handling.
Job Responsibilities:
Essential Job Functions:
Operates wastewater treatment facility. (Class K operator’s license required)
Processes parts through chemical processes to meet production schedule. Coordinates with engineers and supervisors to assist in determining priorities.
Trains and supervises Chemical Operators
Maintains chemical process equipment
Performs chemical analysis and testing
Prepares manifests and arranges for chemical disposal. Oversees sanitary waste water treatment operations
Trouble shoots on metallurgical processes as required
Responsible for maintenance of equipment and tools in supervised area
Evaluates and recommends equipment for purchase
Maintains all required paperwork and documentation
Insures and monitors all chemical processes to be in compliance with all Federal, State and Local laws and regulations.
Maintains compliance with Company policies, safety standards and good housekeeping practices.

Supervisory Responsibilities: Chemical Operators
Qualification Requirements: Bachelors of Science degree in chemistry or chemical engineering or the equivalent in experience. Five years’ minimum experience in plating processes, metallurgical chemistry, waste treatment, chemical research. Knowledge of all EPA and OSHA regulations is a definite plus, as well as having held a class K wastewater treatment operator’s license.
Working Environment: Manufacturing working with chemicals
Company Description
About Richardson Electronics : Richardson Electronics (NASDAQ: RELL) is a leading global provider of engineered solutions, power grid and microwave tubes and related consumables; power conversion and RF and microwave components and replacement parts for diagnostic imaging equipment; and customized display solutions. Founded in 1947 and headquartered just outside of Chicago (LaFox, IL), we employ over 350 people worldwide and maintain stocking locations in the U.S., Europe, Asia and South America. We offer superb prospects for professional growth, along with a competitive salary, healthcare benefits, and 401k.The Company provides solutions and adds value through design-in support, system integration, prototype design and manufacturing, testing, logistics, and aftermarket technical service and repair through its global infrastructure. Learn more about how we are celebrating our past and building our future at www.rell.com.

